# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Frontend production environment (committed to git)
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# This file is loaded when Vite builds in production mode (Cloudflare Pages
# build). It contains ONLY non-secret public URLs. Real secrets are set via
# the Cloudflare Pages dashboard → Settings → Environment Variables.
#
# Per-developer / per-environment overrides go in .env.local (gitignored).
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# Backend API (Rust + Axum on Fly.io). DO NOT include /api suffix —
# request paths in src/lib/api/config.ts already include /api.
VITE_API_URL=https://revolution-trading-pros-api.fly.dev
VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://revolution-trading-pros-api.fly.dev
VITE_WS_URL=wss://revolution-trading-pros-api.fly.dev

# Site metadata
VITE_SITE_NAME=Revolution Trading Pros
VITE_SITE_URL=https://revolution-trading-pros.pages.dev

# Cloudflare R2 CDN (public bucket).
VITE_CDN_URL=https://pub-2e5bd1b702b440bd888a0fc47f3493ae.r2.dev

# Build-mode signal.
ENVIRONMENT=production

# ─── DEVELOPER ACCESS LIST ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# These emails are treated as superadmins by the frontend role helpers
# (frontend/src/lib/config/roles.ts). They MUST also be set on the backend
# via Fly secrets (DEVELOPER_EMAILS, SUPERADMIN_EMAILS) for the bypass to
# work on the API side.
#
# These values are committed to git and visible in the bundled JS — only
# include emails that are OK to be public. Treat this as a hint to the
# frontend, not a security boundary; the backend enforces the real check.
VITE_DEVELOPER_EMAILS=welberribeirodrums@gmail.com
VITE_SUPERADMIN_EMAILS=welberribeirodrums@gmail.com
